Logo tips
An RSO Logo must be unique. You may not edit/add a George Mason University logo. To follow
University branding guidelines:

1. Do not use any version of Mason, GMU, or George Mason. If an RSO chooses to include the
   university name, it must only be after your RSO name as "at George Mason University."
2. "At George Mason University" cannot be located before "at George Mason University."
   oYou can use "at" or the @ symbol.
3. RSOs cannot use any official GMU logo, trademark, Patriot, retired logos (such as the feather
   logo), or the University seal.

