How to Edit Registration Form

_The person who submitted the Registration Form can edit the application_

1. Log into Mason360 > Home > My Activity > My Survey/Forms
2. Locate the Form you Submitted in list (New RSO Registration) >
   Click on “Edit” > Change Information as needed > Click SUBMIT
   Possible Tags on the Form Indicating Issues:  
   • Pending Approval: Waiting on all tasks to be completed
   • Draft: Was not submitted for review
   • Approved: Has been reviewed and Registration has been finalized.
   Only edit the form if changing the 25Live Representatives listed and
   email rso@gmu.edu.
   • Rejected: Email sent with explanation from RSO Lead Team

New RSO Next Steps

Once your club is approved, you can expect a couple of additional processes to occur.
University Events Assign a 25Live Account
• 25Live is the university-wide event and academic scheduling system and is available at http://25live.gmu.edu. All space
for events on campus must be requested through University Events.
ORG Codes
• Fiscal Services works with our office to create ORG Codes. The code is typically a number that has a letter and 6
numbers (ex:Wxxxxx).
• This code is associated with your RSO's account to keep a track of any Student Funding Board Requests, and 25Live will
also need your ORG Code for room reservations.
• To find your ORG Code, go to the "Files" section of your organization's Mason360 page on the left-hand side.
Please allow a couple of weeks after the registration window ends for the offices to process this information and reach out
to your organization.
FALL 2025 New RSOs:
• Your ORG CODE has been created. If it is not listed on your Mason360, please email rso@gmu.edu.
